section.para:
The APIs for this are part of the LowLevelCAS.  The controlling APIs all return an instance
      of AutoClosable, which can be used to reset the setting to its previous value.
      A recommended way of using these is with the Java try with resources construct: 
    try (AutoClosable w = llcas.ll_enableV2IdRefs) {
  ... some operations
} // automatically restores previous value

section.programlisting:
// set the mode    
AutoClosable ll_enableV2IdRefs()

// same, but with explicit set or reset of the mode
AutoClosable ll_enableV2IdRefs(true/false)

// return true if the mode is enabled
boolean is_ll_enableV2IdRefs()

// set the default    
AutoClosable LowLeveCas.ll_defaultV2IdRefs()

// same, but with explicit set or reset of the mode
AutoClosable LowLeveCas.ll_defaultV2IdRefs(true/false)

// return true if the mode is enabled
boolean LowLeveCas.is_ll_defaultV2IdRefs()
